  "description": "The 2025 debut from the Indesit brand is a medium-budget two-chamber refrigerator with the freezer compartment located at the bottom. The model can appeal even to large families, as its total usable capacity reaches 386 liters. It features a body height of 202 cm and a typical width of 59.5 cm. Both compartments of the unit employ a static cooling system, which, among other things, implies the need for periodic manual defrosting. The Indesit INKS 1401 S4U1 refrigerator includes a 120-liter freezer with three pull-out bins for organizing food storage and a modest freezing capacity of 6 kg per day. In the absence of electricity, the cold should be preserved here for up to 24 hours. The 266-liter fridge compartment has 5 open shelves, made from durable tempered glass — they can handle substantial weight (up to 100 kg each). There's also a pull-out vegetable drawer and four full-width door baskets. Other features include simple controls — a rotary switch for adjusting the refrigerator compartment temperature, a concealed door handle, a moderate noise level (up to 38 dB), and A++ energy consumption: the appliance will use up 247 kWh per year. <b>The Indesit INKS 1401 S4U1's <u>ample 386-liter capacity</u> and <u>simple controls</u> make it <u>ideal for large families</u>. The <u>durable glass shelves</u> ensuring reliability and <u>concealed door handle</u> add to its sleek design.</b>",
